// Adversarial: BumpForce(2.5) fires on every Bumped event in a Corridor layout under
// extreme chaos (0.9). Corridor geometry guarantees near-continuous wall bounces, and the
// high chaos probability drives frequent bump attempts including during dashes. Each bump
// force application compounds the launch velocity applied to the bolt on the next bump.
// The adversarial risk: if BumpForce values accumulate without being reversed (e.g. an
// Until wrapper isn't present, so each Bumped permanently adds to ActiveBumpForces), the
// effective force multiplier grows without bound and the bolt's post-bump velocity
// exceeds BoltMaxSpeed. BoltSpeedAccurate is the primary detector; BoltInBounds catches
// position corruption if the high-speed bolt escapes CCD. NoNaN covers overflow.
// 5000 frames of extreme chaos ensures hundreds of bumps and force applications.
(
    breaker: "Aegis",
    layout: "Corridor",
    input: Chaos((action_prob: 0.9)),
    max_frames: 5000,
    disallowed_failures: [BoltInBounds, BoltSpeedAccurate, BreakerCountReasonable, BreakerInBounds, NoNaN],
    allowed_failures: None,
    debug_setup: None,
    allow_early_end: false,
    seed: 2357,
    initial_effects: [
        Stamp(Bolt, When(Bumped, Fire(BumpForce((2.5))))),
    ],
)
